title: For Sale:  1943 M1 Carbine - National Postal Meter
postcontent: National Postal Meter M1 Carbine w/ original Underwood barrel labeled 9-43. The Good - It was updated at some point after the war, as most were, except for the barrel band. Comes with new USGI front sight that has not been sanded/filed and was professionally installed by Wright Armory. Comes with one 15-round magazine and six 30-round magazines. Also has windage and elevation adjustable rear sight, sling, and oiler. The Bad - At some point, someone tried to "customize" this carbine by adding a side-mounted scope mount, refinishing the stock to a lighter color, and adding a recoil reducing buttpad on the stock. When I acquired the carbine, I took it straight to the aforementioned gunsmiths and had them profesionally remove the scopemount. You will see where the markings on the front of the receiver are no longer there due to that process, the rear markings and serial number are intact on the receiver. It is also missing the USGI buttplate. The carbine is perfectly usable as-is, it is a good shooter. If someone wanted to make it "correct", a new stock would need to be sourced. The price I am asking reflects that; NPM M1 Carbines with all matching parts and in original condition regularly go for $1,100+No trades. No shipping at this time. Face-to-face in the valley with a valid Arizona driver's license. Permit to carry and/or Mil/LEO preferred.
